        "description": "<p>This plugin enable Automatic Background Updates for WordPress core (minor and major versions), Themes and Plugins.</p>\n",
        "installation": "<p>In most cases you can install automatically from WordPress.org.</p>\n<p>However, if you install this manually, follow these steps:<br />\n1. Create the directory &#8216;auto-update&#8217; in your &#8216;/wp-content/plugins/&#8217; directory<br />\n2. Upload all the plugin&#8217;s file to the newly created directory<br />\n3. Activate the plugin through the &#8216;Plugins&#8217; menu in WordPress</p>\n<p>Note: There is no &#8220;control panel&#8221; for this plugin.</p>\n",
